{{Politics of Guatemala}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Guatemala]] on 30 January 1994.<ref name=N1>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p323 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref> It followed a [[1993 Guatemalan constitutional crisis|constitutional crisis]] and an attempted [[self-coup]] on 25 May 1993 by President [[Jorge Serrano Elías]]. Among the reforms was a plan to reduce the parliamentary term of the current government.<ref name=DN>Nohlen, p330</ref> The changes were approved by 83.9% of voters, although voter turnout was just 15.9%.<ref name=DN/>
